
            Video
            The country where being a climate activist is a lonely job
            Almost 80% of Poland's electricity is generated by burning coal and around 400,000 people are involved in the coal industry. We spoke with climate activist Patryk Bialas about the challenges faced by Poland in becoming greener. A UN climate conference in Katowice, Poland will address the country's reliance on the coal industry in order to meet aims set by the Paris climate accord in 2015.Video by David Shukman, Ed Habershon and Duncan Stone
                
                        03 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
